      "writtenOn": "2019-09-26T23:04:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Nit: Parse doesn\u0027t quite seem to describe the behavior. Parsing is usually taking some input where we don\u0027t already know the structure, and analyzing its structure.\n\nWe have the structure here already, we\u0027re just converting it to another structure. Put another way, I would actually expect \"parse\" to apply more to the action of converting the JSON input (which is structured, we just don\u0027t know what that structure is yet) to a structured GTestResults.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 93,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 93,
        "endChar": 28
      },
      "revId": "2df789ad38dbf654cca1da25effff6649a53f51a",
